    "body": "Hi @churik are we sure we want that behaviour (user avatar always at the very beginning of the chat history) ?\r\nAs the current user status is displayed in the user avatar and the current user status is something which can be changed and user would want to communicate that to other, it would be very hard for him to actually do that in chat with let's say 1000 old messages - nobody would see the user avatar and his/her actual status unless scrolling to the very top of the conversation, quite impractical.\r\n\r\nIn my opinion the whole idea of displaying User avatar + status as a normal message in stream with all others is wrong - we would ideally want that information to be always available to the user when he is typing/scrolling/looking at the chat, so it should be pinned to one place, but let's have @andmironov have a final word about that :)\r\n",
