    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@andmironov the question is more about the situation when we have many messages in chat (message history spans several days). We can then do some choices:\r\n1. (Current behavior) Always pin user message (with his/her photo & current status) to the last message group (current day messages) - this makes sense from the usability view, as whenever recipient wants to look-up current status (expression of mood) of the sender, he just needs to scroll over today's messages and he/she can see it. On the other hand, it's quite disrupting from the visual point of view and feels weird.  \r\n2. Always pin the user message to the oldest message group in the chat, so it's effectively always the first message in the chat - it doesn't look that weird, but in any longer conversation (say conversation spanning multiple weeks/months), the ability to look-up status of the sender is virtually lost for the recipient - he/she would have to scroll to the very first message in the chat to see it, not fun.\r\n3. Get rid of the user message with photo and chat altogether and find some other place where to show sender status so it's always pinned on the screen no matter how the recipient scroll through the messages - user name & photo are already displayed in the status bar, so we just need to find some place for the user status :)",
